KRA detectives on Thursday nabbed four men suspected to be part of a fuel adulteration syndicate. Detectives stormed a yard in Nairobi's Mowlem area, where they found 55 drums of petrol, diesel and paraffin. A generator, fuel tank, two fuel tankers and a truck were also found in the yard, popularly known as 'Macharia's yard'. The suspects alleged the fuel was being supplied by local depots. More follows....